  protein: 41 g
---

Peel and finely chop the @garlic{6%cloves}. Peel the @ginger{3}(peeled) using the edge of a #spoon{} and very finely chop (or grate). Chop the @spring onions{6}(into micro-thin discs, separating the white and green parts), separate the @broccoli{2}(separated into florets).

Mix together the @soy sauce{6%tbsp} with 3 tbsp of @?sugar{3%tbsp}(if you have some) and the @sesame oil{2%tbsp}. Add half the garlic and two-thirds of the ginger and keep stirring until the sugar dissolves. Next stir in the whites of the spring onions.

> This is your bulgogi mix.

Pour half the mixture over the @British beef mince{500%g}, mix thoroughly and leave for as long as possible.

> This would be a great step to do well in advance - we left it for an hour and it made a HUGE difference to the flavour, but let your appetite make the decision!

Boil a medium-sized #pot{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Once the water comes to a boil add in the broccoli. Bring back to the boil and leave for ~{2%minutes}. Lift the broccoli from the water and keep to the side - don't throw the water away!

Pour out all but 700ml of the boiling water. Place your @basmati rice{2%cups} into this pot of boiling water and put a #lid{} on. Cook for ~{10%minutes} on the lowest heat possible, then remove from the heat for ~{10%minutes}.

> Do not touch the lid until 20 mins are up, to ensure the rice is cooked perfectly.

Heat @oil{2%tsp} on high heat in a #frying pan{}. Once really hot add in your beef bulgogi mix and fry for around ~{4-5%minutes} until cooked.

> Patrick slightly undercooked his to keep it really juicy.

> If you only have a small pan don't overcrowd it - cook the beef in batches to brown it off.

Once the beef bulgogi is cooked, remove it from the pan and keep it warm. Drain some of the oil from the pan and get it really hot. Throw in the remaining garlic and ginger then after ~{15%seconds} add in the broccoli. Cook for ~{2%minutes} - you want it to be a little crunchy when you eat it.

Separate the grains of rice with a #fork{} and stir through the greens of the spring onions. Serve the bulgogi beef with the rice, the broccoli on the side, a sprinkling of @sesame seeds{1.5%tbsp} and the rest of the sauce mixture drizzled over the top.